    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-05-23</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-08-07T16:28:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Emergency Gas Price Relief Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to reduce highway motor fuel excise taxes by 10 cents per gallon, beginning on the date when the retail price for gasoline is greater than $3.00 per gallon and ending when such price is less than $2.50 per gallon (reduction period). Allows a tax credit or refund of such excise tax to a taxpayer for floor stocks of highway motor fuels held by dealers prior to the reduction period.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
